<emphasis box="[830,849,506,529]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">et</emphasis>
); ventral trichobothria on patella number 32–34; internal trichobothria on chela number 3, accessory external trichobothrium 
<emphasis box="[1000,1025,567,590]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">ea</emphasis>
on chela absent, ventral trichobothria on chela number 12–15. Pedipalp very densely hirsute, mainly on chela. Granules on manus of pedipalp conical and pointed. Lobe of chela granulated with the same intensity as whole dorsal surface of chela. External surface of chela granulate but without carinae. Chela of male length/ width ratio is 1.56. Pectinal teeth number 
<quantity box="[830,932,782,805]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.953" metricValueMax="5.334" metricValueMin="4.572" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" unit="in" value="19.5" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="18.0">18–21 in</quantity>
both sexes. Dorsal carinae on first through fourth metasomal segments granulate and terminate in a larger tooth most conspicuous on fourth segment. Spiniform formula of tarsomere II = 7/4: 7-8/4: 8-9/5-6: 8-9/6-7. Tarsomere II with 3 spines on inclined anteroventral surface. Length to width ratio of male 5th metasomal segment = 2.29.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[830,1441,1030,1912]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
COMMENTS. 
<bibRefCitation author="POCOCK" box="[1027,1296,1030,1053]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="392 - 407" refId="ref6067" refString="POCOCK, R. I. 1897. Solifugae, Scorpiones, Chilopoda, and Diplopoda. The first expedition from Somaliland to Lake Lamu. Appendix C to Donaldson Smith`s Through Unknown African Countries, Greenwood Press, Publishers, New York, 1897: 392 - 407." type="journal article" year="1897">Pocock (1897: 398–400)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smithi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">P. smithi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from a female 1 04 mm long from Turfa and a male 
<quantity box="[901,1001,1091,1114]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" unit="mm" value="105.0">105 mm</quantity>
long, probably also from Turfa in &quot;Somaliland&quot; and cited also four other specimens from Somaliland, a female 
<quantity box="[1068,1157,1153,1176]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.14" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" unit="mm" value="114.0">114 mm</quantity>
long from Silul, a female 
<quantity box="[830,920,1183,1206]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.06" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" unit="mm" value="106.0">106 mm</quantity>
long from Hargesa (Hargeisa), and a male 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" unit="mm" value="110.0">110 mm</quantity>
long and a young male without a special locality. 
<bibRefCitation author="POCOCK" box="[830,1047,1245,1268]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="392 - 407" refId="ref6067" refString="POCOCK, R. I. 1897. Solifugae, Scorpiones, Chilopoda, and Diplopoda. The first expedition from Somaliland to Lake Lamu. Appendix C to Donaldson Smith`s Through Unknown African Countries, Greenwood Press, Publishers, New York, 1897: 392 - 407." type="journal article" year="1897">Pocock (1897: 399)</bibRefCitation>
wrote about these four other specimens: &quot;Four other examples were also obtained, and these differ from the two describing in having the legs reddish brown or reddish green in color instead of a bright redish yellow&quot;. 
<bibRefCitation author="POCOCK" box="[1072,1283,1367,1390]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="392 - 407" refId="ref6067" refString="POCOCK, R. I. 1897. Solifugae, Scorpiones, Chilopoda, and Diplopoda. The first expedition from Somaliland to Lake Lamu. Appendix C to Donaldson Smith`s Through Unknown African Countries, Greenwood Press, Publishers, New York, 1897: 392 - 407." type="journal article" year="1897">Pocock (1897: 400)</bibRefCitation>
also cited 
<specimenCount pageId="15" pageNumber="14" type="immature">two immature</specimenCount>
examples from Ahdeh and Boholgarshan which &quot;apparently belonging to this species&quot;. Later 
<bibRefCitation author="POCOCK" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="55 - 63" refId="ref6117" refString="POCOCK, R. I. 1900. On a collection of insects and arachnids made in 1895 and 1897 by Mr. C. A. V. Peel, F. Z. S. in Somailand, with descriptions of new species. 10. General list of the scorpions of Somaliland and the Boran Country. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1900: 55 - 63." type="book chapter" year="1900">Pocock (1900: 58)</bibRefCitation>
cited &quot;Hargeisa, Silul, Abdeh, and Turfa in Somaliland&quot; as localities of 
<taxonomicName box="[1157,1252,1490,1513]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smithi">
<emphasis box="[1157,1252,1490,1513]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">P. smithi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[830,1441,1030,1912]" lastBlockId="18.[192,802,199,590]" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
The first author (FK) studied and designated as 
<typeStatus box="[830,928,1551,1574]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">lectotype</typeStatus>
the female from Turfa (
<figureCitation box="[1189,1268,1551,1574]" captionStart="Figures 26–27" captionStartId="10.[192,278,1825,1848]" captionTargetBox="[191,1440,191,1795]" captionTargetId="figure-11@10.[192,1439,192,1795]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figures 26–27: Pandinurus smithi (Pocock, 1897). Figure 26. Female lectotype and original labels. Scale bar: 10 mm for the female lectotype. Figure 27. Male, at the locality, Ethiopia, 55 km S of Degehbur, 07°49'27.2&quot;N 43°41'56.3&quot;E, 1053 m a.s.l." pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
) but incorrectly cited the type locality Silul (
<bibRefCitation author="KOVARIK" box="[1170,1396,1582,1605]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="133 - 159" refId="ref5454" refString="KOVARIK, F. 2003. Scorpions of Djibouti, Eritrea, Ethiopia, and Somalia (Arachnida: Scorpiones), with a key and descriptions of three new species. Acta Societatis Zoologicae Bohemicae, 67: 133 - 159." type="journal article" year="2003">Kovařík, 2003: 152</bibRefCitation>
) or Hargeisa (Kovařík, 2009: 58; 
<bibRefCitation author="KOVARIK" box="[1184,1399,1613,1636]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 18" refId="ref5538" refString="KOVARIK, F. 2011. A review of the subgenus Pandinus Thorell, 1876 with descriptions of two new species from Uganda and Ethiopia (Scorpiones, Scorpionidae). Euscorpius, 129: 1 - 18." type="journal article" year="2011">Kovařík, 2011: 10</bibRefCitation>
; 2; Kovařík et al., 2017: 89). We here correct this error and recognize the type locality of 
<taxonomicName box="[1148,1345,1674,1697]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smithi">
<emphasis box="[1148,1345,1674,1697]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Pandinurus smithi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as Turfa (see 
<figureCitation box="[885,969,1705,1728]" captionStart="Figures 26–27" captionStartId="10.[192,278,1825,1848]" captionTargetBox="[191,1440,191,1795]" captionTargetId="figure-11@10.[192,1439,192,1795]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figures 26–27: Pandinurus smithi (Pocock, 1897). Figure 26. Female lectotype and original labels. Scale bar: 10 mm for the female lectotype. Figure 27. Male, at the locality, Ethiopia, 55 km S of Degehbur, 07°49'27.2&quot;N 43°41'56.3&quot;E, 1053 m a.s.l." pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). Another problem is that Pocock located Turfa and all other localities of the cited specimens in Somaliland which is accepted by all recent authors. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 36" captionStartId="16.[192,268,1766,1789]" captionTargetBox="[191,1437,191,1737]" captionTargetId="figure-47@16.[192,1436,192,1736]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figure 36: Map of Africa from 1885 (origin https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:African_map_1885.jpg) with the place where Turfa and Silul are located marked by red point." pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
shows a map of Africa published in 1885, which explains why Pocock cited the localities as these places in Somaliland and titled his 1897 paper &quot;The first expedition from Somaliland to lake Lamu&quot;. However, nowadays the type locality (Turfa) and the locality Silul are located in 
<collectingCountry box="[352,442,230,253]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
while Hargesa (Hargeisa) is the capital of Somaliland (
<figureCitation box="[435,515,260,283]" captionStart="Figure 37" captionStartId="17.[192,268,1689,1712]" captionTargetBox="[192,1439,192,1659]" captionTargetId="figure-132@17.[192,1439,192,1659]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 37: A. Map with marked places where types of P. smithi were collected, originally published by Smith (1897). B. Actual map of Horn of Africa with marked discussed localities. 1–4. Localities cited by Pocock (1897) except locality &quot;Ahdeh (Abdeh)&quot; which we has not found (1. Turfa, type locality of P. smithi, 2. Silul, 3. Hargesa, 4. Boholgarshan.). 5–7. Localities where the first and the third authors collected Pandinurus specimens (5. Locality 11EV, Ethiopia, 55 km S of Degehbur, 07°49'27.2&quot;N 43°41'56.3&quot;E where was collected a male of P. smithi. 6. Locality 17SE, Somaliland, Toon village near Hargeisa, 09°23'30&quot;N 44°07'10&quot;E, the type locality of P. hangarale. 7. Woqooyi Galbeed, 09°11'56&quot;N 44°09'50&quot;E, between Hargeisa and Salahle, the locality of P. hangarale paratype)." pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="16" pageNumber="15" startId="16.[192,268,1766,1789]" targetBox="[191,1437,191,1737]" targetPageId="16">
<paragraph blockId="16.[192,1440,1766,1814]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,312,1766,1789]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">Figure 36:</emphasis>
Map of Africa from 1885 (origin https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:African_map_1885.jpg) with the place where Turfa and Silul are located marked by red point.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption pageId="17" pageNumber="16" startId="17.[192,268,1689,1712]" targetBox="[192,1439,192,1659]" targetPageId="17">
<paragraph blockId="17.[192,1440,1689,1860]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,333,1689,1712]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Figure 37: A</emphasis>
. Map with marked places where types of 
<taxonomicName box="[736,822,1690,1711]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smithi">
<emphasis box="[736,822,1690,1711]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">P. smithi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were collected, originally published by 
<bibRefCitation author="SMITH" box="[1208,1339,1690,1711]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" refId="ref6247" refString="SMITH, A. D. 1897. Through Unknown African Countries; the First Expedition from Somaliland to Lake Lamu. London: Edward Arnold. 471 pp." type="book" year="1897">Smith (1897)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1348,1364,1690,1711]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">B</emphasis>
. Actual map of Horn of Africa with marked discussed localities. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[742,778,1715,1736]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">1–4</emphasis>
. Localities cited by 
<bibRefCitation author="POCOCK" box="[975,1116,1715,1736]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" pagination="392 - 407" refId="ref6067" refString="POCOCK, R. I. 1897. Solifugae, Scorpiones, Chilopoda, and Diplopoda. The first expedition from Somaliland to Lake Lamu. Appendix C to Donaldson Smith`s Through Unknown African Countries, Greenwood Press, Publishers, New York, 1897: 392 - 407." type="journal article" year="1897">Pocock (1897)</bibRefCitation>
except locality &quot;Ahdeh (Abdeh)&quot; which we has not found (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[444,456,1740,1761]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">1</emphasis>
. Turfa, type locality of 
<taxonomicName box="[703,789,1740,1761]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smithi">
<emphasis box="[703,789,1740,1761]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">P. smithi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[802,814,1740,1761]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">2</emphasis>
. Silul, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[889,899,1740,1761]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">3</emphasis>
. Hargesa, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1007,1017,1740,1761]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">4</emphasis>
. Boholgarshan.). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1194,1228,1740,1761]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">5–7</emphasis>
. Localities where the first and the third authors collected 
<taxonomicName box="[552,664,1765,1786]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[552,664,1765,1786]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Pandinurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[791,803,1765,1786]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">5</emphasis>
. Locality 11EV, Ethiopia, 55 km S of Degehbur, 07°49'27.2&quot;N 4 3°41'56.3&quot;E where was collected a male of 
<taxonomicName box="[639,726,1790,1811]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smithi">
<emphasis box="[639,726,1790,1811]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">P. smithi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[741,753,1790,1811]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">6</emphasis>
. Locality 17SE, Somaliland, Toon village near Hargeisa, 09°23'30&quot;N 44°07'10&quot;E, the type locality of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kovařík &amp; Lowe &amp; Mazuch &amp; Awale &amp; Jana" authorityYear="2017" box="[508,633,1815,1836]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hangarale">
<emphasis box="[508,633,1815,1836]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">P. hangarale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[647,659,1815,1836]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">7</emphasis>
. Woqooyi Galbeed, 09°11'56&quot;N 44°09'50&quot;E, between Hargeisa and Salahle, the locality of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kovařík &amp; Lowe &amp; Mazuch &amp; Awale &amp; Jana" authorityYear="2017" box="[296,422,1839,1860]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hangarale">
<emphasis box="[296,422,1839,1860]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">P. hangarale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
paratype).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="18.[192,802,199,590]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">
We suspect that 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pocock, 1897)" baseAuthorityName="Pocock" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[426,802,291,314]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="18" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smithi">
<emphasis box="[426,625,291,314]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Pandinurus smithi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="POCOCK" box="[643,794,291,314]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17" pagination="392 - 407" refId="ref6067" refString="POCOCK, R. I. 1897. Solifugae, Scorpiones, Chilopoda, and Diplopoda. The first expedition from Somaliland to Lake Lamu. Appendix C to Donaldson Smith`s Through Unknown African Countries, Greenwood Press, Publishers, New York, 1897: 392 - 407." type="journal article" year="1897">Pocock, 1897</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
occurs only in 
<collectingCountry box="[357,447,322,345]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
and that the specimens cited by Pocock without a specific locality from Hargesa may belong to a different speices, one described herein as 
<taxonomicName authority="Kovařík &amp; Lowe &amp; Mazuch &amp; Awale &amp; Jana, 2017" authorityName="Kovařík &amp; Lowe &amp; Mazuch &amp; Awale &amp; Jana" authorityYear="2017" box="[192,435,414,437]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="18" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hangarale" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[192,435,414,437]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Pandinurus hangarale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[444,506,414,437]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[444,506,414,437]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
One remaining unresolved question regards the taxonomic position of a female that Pocock recorded from Silul (now 
<collectingCountry box="[593,688,475,498]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
), but that groups with specimens lacking &quot;bright reddish yellow legs&quot;, and 
<specimenCount box="[322,479,536,559]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17" type="immature">two immature</specimenCount>
examples from Ahdeh and Boholgarshan which also were not recently studied.
</paragraph>
